ed by the Colombian state to control and maintain its territory and political legitimacy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aDeath squadszColombia. 0aParamilitary forceszColombia. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  a21st century colombia.  acacique nutibara.  acali cartel.  acolombian cartel.  acolombian control of citizenry.  acolombian death squads.  acolombian drug lords.  acolombian drug trade.  acolombian drug war.  acolombian paramilitary.  acolombian political violence.  acolombian politics.  acolombias drug kingpins.  ahistory of violence in colombia.  aparamilitary action in colombia.  aparamilitary death squads.  astate control in colombia.  aviolence in colombia.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015z97831106211120 cprintz978052028851540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096340540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520963405423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520963405/original  a978-3-11-062111-2  University of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY